content:
With OmniStudio, you can create experiences with guided interactions for your customers and agents using data from Salesforce orgs and external sources.

What Is OmniStudio?

OmniStudio streamlines processes by creating guided user experiences: just what you need and what tasks to complete.

FlexCards display contextual information and provide access to relevant tasks. OmniScripts guide users through sales, service, and other business processes.

Use external data easily with FlexCards and OmniScripts. These data services read, write, transform, calculate, and track data within and outside of Salesforce.

Omnistudio Data Mappers retrieve, transform, and update data. Integration Procedures are declarative, server-side processes that take multiple actions in a single server call.

Simplify your DevOps with tools to deploy changes and manage their dependencies between orgs.

IDX Workbench deploys data packs and Salesforce metadata between orgs or from an org to a Git repository. OmniStudio Build Tool packages and deploys OmniStudio data packs.

OmniStudio has two versions:

*   OmniStudio Standard uses the standard Salesforce object model.
*   OmniStudio for Vlocity uses a custom object model.

See Differences Between OmniStudio and OmniStudio for Vlocity.
title: OmniStudio: A Low-Code Tool for Guided User Experiences
